ZH: 我们明天再见。
EN: Let's meet again tomorrow.

ZH: 他们不停地挥手说再见。
EN: They kept waving and saying goodbye.

ZH: 祝你一路平安，再见。
EN: Have a safe journey, goodbye.

ZH: 他对他的父母道了再见。
EN: He bid farewell to his parents.

ZH: 再见，希望尽早见面。
EN: Goodbye, hope to see you soon.

ZH: 她没有说再见就匆匆离开了。
EN: She left in a hurry without saying goodbye.

ZH: 我们分别时，他轻声说了一句再见。
EN: When we parted, he softly said goodbye.

ZH: 我们最好说声再见。
EN: We better say goodbye.

ZH: 再见了！希望你幸福。
EN: Goodbye! I wish you happiness.

ZH: 缺乏适时的再见，使我感到有些失望。
EN: The lack of a timely goodbye made me feel a bit disappointed.

ZH: 听到他深情的再见，我既难过又感动。
EN: Hearing his heartfelt goodbye, I felt both sad and touched.

ZH: 朋友们饯行时，大家纷纷道再见。
EN: When the friends were seeing them off, everyone said goodbye.

ZH: 他随手泼了一把水，当作再见。
EN: He casually splashed water as a way of saying goodbye.

ZH: 谁也不知道这是否是最后一次再见。
EN: Nobody knows if this will be the last goodbye.

ZH: 就这样啦，再见。
EN: That's it then, goodbye.

ZH: 在车站跟他们道别，终于说了声再见。
EN: Saying goodbye to them at the station, finally I said goodbye.

ZH: 没有一声再见，我就匆忙离去。
EN: I left in a hurry without saying goodbye.

ZH: 他对我们最后怀念时说了一声再见。
EN: He bid us a final farewell when he nostalgia hit him.

ZH: 和平夜晚，星星隐约可见，再见的惆怅笼罩在他们心头。
EN: In the tranquil night, with faintly visible stars, the melancholy of goodbyes lingered in their hearts.

ZH: 不管怎样，我们还是要良好分别，道声再见才是礼貌。
